          <tr id="abs_Siddiqi07c" class="abstract noshow">
            <td colspan="4" ><div align="justify"><b>Abstract</b>: We propose a novel technique for building generative models of real-valued multivariate time series data streams. Such models are of considerable utility as baseline simulators in anomaly detection systems. The proposed algorithm, based on Linear Dynamical Systems (LDS), learns stable parameters efficiently while yeilding more accurate results than previously known methods. The resulting model can be used to generate infinitely long sequences of realistic baselines using small samples of training data.</div></td>
